What you need to know:  Fluorspar Mining Company which operated in Keiyo South constituency in Kimwarer shut its  operations in April 2016 over what it termed a “depressed demand and prices” of fluoride on the global market, leading to lossesA task force was set up by the county government and tasked to collect views from the members of the public over the firm’s closureTask force chairman Joseph Kandie handed over the report to Governor Wisley Rotich, following a series of community engagements